  "text": "Astronomy is commonly referred to as the \"gateway science\" (National Research Council, 2001) in the sense that it provides students with a conduit to get engaged with, and appreciate other sciences. This characteristic of astronomy was echoed in RTSRE 2017 keynote address by Timothy F. Slater, where he highlighted how it can be used as a vehicle to inspire students to appreciate science and encourage them to pursue science, rather than creating astronomers per se. This is illustrated in the recent work of [CITATION_1] who reveal the significant positive changes in student perceptions of science after undertaking an astronomy education program.",
